      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "DENVER, Feb. 14-All shopmen,\nengineers, conductors and brake\nmen on the Denver & Rio Grande\nrailroad may go on strike, which\nmight involve all the Gould lines,\non March IA. The following order\nhas aroused intense feeling among\nthe men:\n\n\neffective March IA the rules and\nregulations governing employing\nmen in departments, mechanics,\nboilermakers and helpers, will be\nabolished on the Denver & Rio\nGrande.\"\n\n\nMeetings of union men have been\nheld to discuss the order all over\nthe state. Committee have been\nappointed to attempt to get new\ncontracts between the unions and\nthe road, but if they cannot be Sc\ncured a huge strike may be par.\nticipated, as the men will not stand\nfor the open shop."
    }
  ]
